{
  "text": "Because HER2/neu-induced breast neoplasia is suppressed by either pharmacologic inhibition or genetic ablation of the PG synthase Cox-2 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] 24) , increasing mammary PG levels would be predicted to accelerate HER2/neu-driven mammary tumor formation. We speculate that 5010 chow may contain components that increase mammary eicosanoid levels. Consistent with this notion, dietary administration of celecoxib reduced mammary PGE 2 by only 34% in animals consuming AIN-76A (Table 3) , compared with the 47% reduction we previously reported for 5010-fed animals (20) , suggesting that animals consuming 5010 chow may have elevated basal mammary eicosanoid levels.",
